KCSE candidates in Borabu subcounty, Nyamira county, have received stationery from the Dr Kambi Foundation.Dr Nyandoro Kambi, the founder, donated geometry sets, clip boards and pencils to all public schools in Borabu constituency.The Nairobi-based lawyer also has a school feeding programme for standard eight pupils. This is one way of giving back to society and improving the performance of candidates in the national exams. Education of the young generation is the only reward we can give to pupils from poor backgrounds, Kambi said. However, critics have termed his good deeds a campaign strategy. Kambi denied the allegations.